This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to identify relevant information and assemble it into coherent narratives. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of neural models, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses clustering and similarity measures, which are relevant to cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval and search, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with the challenges of dealing with messy and distributed data, which is relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
